name: media_png_valid_minimal_rgba_1x1
description: |
  A tiny, conforming 1x1 RGBA PNG used as a baseline for the PNG cases in this
  directory. It has the normal PNG signature, a single IHDR, one IDAT containing
  a complete zlib stream for one transparent pixel, and IEND. The other PNG
  inputs pair against this one when they intentionally differ by one validation
  rule.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The format rules are from the PNG specification:
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "valid-png"
  - "baseline"
---
